Investigative Report by Reuters Reveals the Last Days of Fugitive Syrian President Bashar al-Assad and the Role of the UAE in Smuggling His Wealth from Syria

### English Text Summary:
An investigative report by Reuters uncovers the final days of the fugitive Syrian President Bashar al-Assad and highlights the involvement of the United Arab Emirates in facilitating the smuggling of his wealth out of Syria. The report suggests that the UAE played a significant role in assisting Assad in escaping with his assets. The program airs daily episodes at 3 PM GMT from Monday to Friday, and viewers can also access trending stories through a provided link.

